text: Alfred Park (15 April 1840 - 16 January 1924) was an Australian cricketer. He played three first-class matches for New South Wales between 1861/62 and 1868/69. ==See also== * List of New South Wales representative cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1840 births Category:1924 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:New South Wales cricketers Category:Cricketers from Tasmania
